The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Karim relieved
                                                   Karim relieved
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Mohun Bagans Karim Bencharifa was a much-relieved man on Monday after his sides 2-1 victory over United SC.         
	We were going through a lean patch lately. The AFC Cup matches came at such a crucial time  But Im happy with my teams performance today (Monday). United are a tough team, said the Moroccan. He added: The win will instil confidence in the team. I am not thinking about what the other teams are doing as we have to concentrate on the remaining matches.         
	United coach, Subrata Bhattacharya blamed poor refereeing for the loss. Both the Bagan goals were the result of faulty refereeing, said Subrata. He also rued missing three of his key players  Murithala Ali, Daniel and Subhasih Roychowdhury  in the match saying their presence could have given them at least a point.                                                                                                                       
